üéØ How to answer architect questions (RULE OF 3)

Always structure answers as:

Acknowledge the constraint

Explain the core principle

Give a practical solution

Example:

‚ÄúGiven a hard rate limit, we must apply backpressure. Practically, I‚Äôd use a bounded leaky bucket enforced at the ingress.‚Äù

üß† One universal sentence that saves you

If you ever get stuck, say:

‚ÄúAt this point it becomes a system design and capacity problem, so we must bound the system or degrade gracefully.‚Äù

